# =============================================================================
# SETUP (do this once per machine / folder)
# =============================================================================
# 1) Copy this whole file into the SAME folder as:
#      upload-songdata-github-release.ps1
# 2) Rename the copy to exactly:
#      upload-songdata-github-release.secrets.txt
# 3) Edit the TWO lines marked "EDIT BELOW" (see the numbered rules).
# 4) In Windows Notepad use: File -> Save As -> Encoding: UTF-8
#    (avoid "UTF-16" / Unicode — that breaks the token line.)
# =============================================================================

# --- LINE 1 (required): Personal Access Token ---------------------------
# Meaning of "replace ghp_REPLACE_ME":
#   The text "ghp_REPLACE_ME" is ONLY a sample. DELETE that entire sample string,
#   then paste YOUR real token as the ONLY thing on this line.
#   Do NOT keep the letters REPLACE_ME. Do NOT add quotes unless the whole
#   token is wrapped once in '...' or "..." (the script strips one pair).
#   Alternative form (optional): GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_yourRealTokenHere
#
# Your real token is shown ONCE when you create it on GitHub (you cannot see
# it again). It usually starts with ghp_ or github_pat_
#
# EDIT BELOW — put your real PAT on the next line (delete ghp_REPLACE_ME first):
ghp_REPLACE_ME

# --- LINE 2 (recommended): GitHub repository ----------------------------
# Format: owner/repo   Example: octocat/Hello-World
# Must match the repository where you upload the Release.
# Alternative form (optional): GITHUB_REPOSITORY=owner/repo
#
# EDIT BELOW — replace owner/repo with yours:
owner/repo
